description: It's the triumphant debut of the ongoing, full-color adventures of comics' original female archaeologist/explorer! Join Gina Diggers and her lycanthrope sister, Cheetah, in a whirlpool of action and excitement as they dive to the bottom of the Pacific Ocean in search of Muthia - a fabled floating city that sank 4,000 years ago. Treasure and ancient secrets await, but it won't be easy getting them. Not only is Lord "Peewee" Talon hot on Gina's trail with a sub full of goons, not only is the mysterious shape-shifter Taur lurking in the sunken ruins... but Cheetah forgot to "go" before getting in the submarine!

Gina's journey into the sunken continent of Muthia is complicated by the sudden appearance of one of her arch-rival treasure hunters, Erwin "Peewee" Talon... the 10 year- old biogenetic engineer. Peewee and his genetically enhanced bodyguards, in their desire to reach Muthia's ancient archives first, release Muthia's guardian spirit Grata, who has spent the centuries watching television through mystic receivers, has always wanted to be a gameshow host... and makes Gina and her group battle Peewee and his group in a deadly gameshow of his design for the secrets of Muthia's archives! Little does either contestant team know that Grata has no intention of letting either party win!

Gina and the group begin to wrap up their expedition into Muthia. Their only prize from the harrowing experience is a simple black cauldron. Only when a mysterious mystic artifact collector visits Gina's lab does she begin to suspect the cauldron's true nature. Unfortunately, this collector has brought the means to take the cauldron by force! Gina and her lab's new defenses are soon overwhelmed. Her only hope for survival (with the cauldron) is to contact Britanny, who is baking cookies upstairs in the kitchen - and Brit's made it clear that she's not to be disturbed 'til she's finished!

Britanny discovers the true purpose of the "parting gift" she received from the ancient "game show" trap in the ruins of Muthia. The harmless, worthless square of tinted glass is actually a strange magical item that lets Brit gaze into her distant past, but does not let her control which part of the past she sees! Through this glass, she sees the fate of her werecheetah clan and the events that left her the last of the werecheetahs!

Gina takes the day off at the beach and everyone tags along! Unfortunately word has gotten out that Gina is close to unraveling the secrets of the Djinni- Stone, and a few of Gina's seedier competitors decide to take advantage of her taking a vacation by stealing her only link to the Djinni-Stone.

It's time for the Annual World Explorers Society Banquet, where adventurers like Gina Diggers, Penny Pincer and Ryan Tabbot with scores of others like them gather to compare notes and give applause and recognition to their own.

Gina has normally avoided the banquet because she felt she had better things to do, and nothing really worthwhile to share, until this year,........

Gina discovers the second of the five ancient cauldrons in the outback of Australia. Unfortunately, the mystic cauldron happens to be in the lair of Australia's legendary monster, the Bunyip ? and he's invited the Yeti, Sasquatch, and the Jersey Devil over for tea and biscuits! Things get a bit complicated when a few annoying little acquaintances from Ireland, who've decided to follow Gina's lead and become explorers, come looking for the cauldron of fire as well, since rumor has it that it's made out of pure gold!

Part two of the World Explorer Societies annual banquet, and the annual end of the awards ceremony "Brawl" has started early.

With everyone choosing a side, either with Gina Diggers or Against her.

In the confusion Some like Pee Wee and Fauntleroy try to take advantage of the chaos to further their own plans,... while people like Gina just want to make someone pay for spoiling their great moment.

.....Someone might get hurt.

However, Brit's real purpose for this fishing trip is to catch the bluefin tuna she has named "Scarface"... the very same tuna she caught before... the same one that swallowed her wedding ring and got away! Suddenly, a giant walking Moai statue from Easter Island appears... just when Scarface finally takes the bait!

Gina Diggers, fresh from winning the Explorer of the Year Award, has gathered her fellow adventurers; Penny, Ace, Stryyp, and Seance; to explore the ruins of Uhm Di Turrok. "The Halls of the Extremely Dead"

Unknown to the Diggers team. Fauntleroy, the evil dragon turned human, searching for the same treasure. As these two forces search for the artifact that holds the secrets to the ancient, magical race of the Djinni. A mysterious third party watches both of them.

description:
As Julia begins her fight , the Northern Edge-Guard infiltrate the lair of her arch-enemy G'nolga, the current Armsmaster. They soon find themselves in mortal danger, unable to use their magic weapons or powers. Meanwhile, Julia discovers that the Renewing Breath has had some disturbing side effects.

Julia now has the chance to represent the Barbarian Clan in the Arms Master tournament, but the battle with her mother has come with a cost. The tournament has finally started, and Julia comes face to face with the woman who robbed her of her rightful title, G'nolga.

The Northern Edge Guard has slipped in undercover to sniff out Tirant's plot, but must get past the lethal villain, Rook. Sheila just wishes she had more 'coverage'.

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover, other

description:
Fauntleroy... a God?! ? Dao and Madrid lead Gina to the magic nexus, the asteroid which fell to earth 65 million years ago, and somehow infused the world with the power of magic. However, Fauntleroy has been waiting for this opportunity! He and Efreeti seize control of the nexus, gaining its awful powers. Stryyp and Britanny are on the way to help, but they may be too late!

Gina, Stryyp, and Penny face off with Fauntleroy's two wives inside the ruins of Uhm Di Turrok. Outside, Seance battles alone against the powerful Fauntleroy. There are still many questions left. Who is this mysterious watcher? How can they survive these ruins swarmed with death traps? Will Gina survive the consequences of this adventure? Britanny is going to be TICKED!!

person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover, other

description:
Julia reveals that she lost her title as "Armsmaster of Jade" while dueling G'nolga in the Tournament of Arms. As the new Armsmaster, Gnolga invoked authority over all master fighters of Jade and declared Julia an enemy of the realm ? a loophole clause in the Armsmaster codex which G'nolga exploited and all master fighters must obey. Julia's family and friends on Jade were all arrested and imprisoned, and Julia was forced to flee from the realm in disgrace. Now she has finished healing and is ready to challenge G'nolga for the title of Armsmaster, rescue her loved ones and save Jade from Gnolga's tyranny! But first she must find her old teacher, Master Leepe, and seek his advice!

The Diggers sisters have all gathered home from their separate adventures. Britanny may have failed so far, but Gina is all ready to start her next quest. Before anything can happen their mother, Julia, appears. She shares with them the tale of how she lost her title of Arms Master, and her plan to reclaim it. It's going to be...groovy.

But to survive the tournament, she must learn a special technique, which means she must go back to her lecherous old martial arts teacher!

description:
Julia begins her long battle through the tournament of arms to regain her title as Armsmaster of Jade, but the other contestants aren't making it easy for her. Meanwhile, her mother Brunhildegard is ambushed by four armsmasters who, under G'nolga's orders, are tasked with capturing the 400-lb Amazon. They say it's not over 'til the fat lady sings, but what happens when she has to fight off four of Jade's best warriors?

The tournament to decide who is the Arms Master of the Jade Realm is just about to begin, and a plot is forming to conquer the realm. The title will decide the fate of this world.

Julia must find the training she needs to defeat her life long rival, G'nolga; but Theodore is enraged to see his wife has returned to her lecherous sensei, Master Leap.

Julia Diggers has walked into the hornets nest. Once a great hero. Now she is seen as a coward. Even her own Barbarian Clan is denying her the chance to fight for her former title of Arms Master. The one person standing in her way is the a foe she never wished to fight, but she must defeat no matter the cost: her own mother.

  2. "Attack of the Ultimate Warrior!" written by Cary Bates, penciled by Curt Swan, inked by Frank Chiaramonte, colored by Gene D'Angelo and lettered by Ben Oda.
  3. "Daily Planet" Volume 79 Issue 8 the week of February 19, 1979 edited by Bob Rozakis, production by Anthony Tollin and lettered by Typeset. Featuring the upcoming issue of World's Finest Comics #257. Plus, "Ask the Answer Man".
  4. "Hembeck" written, penciled and inked by Fred Hembeck.

Notes:

  • This issue contains the Hostess Superhero Ad, Wonder Woman in "The Golden Treasure".
  • Perry White and Jimmy Olsen flashback from Action Comics #494.

Previously, letters threatening to reveal Superman’s secrets had arrived in the Daily Planet. Perry White had sent Kent and Lois to Smallville to cover the story. Now they have arrived in Smallville and have experienced forces beyond their understanding. Superman got busted by an alien warrior at a waterfall.

Now Superman recovers from the skull-shattering blow struck by the Dwalu and flies back home. There he manages to duck Lois’ questions and gets down to draw a sketch of the Dwalu. Chief Parker prepares his infra-red camera once more to photograph the ghost. But Clark is disturbed and prefers to remain alone.

Superman goes down to his underground chamber and keeps the sketch inside the secret niche. Next he goes to sleep. But later that night, an unearthly energy emanates from the metal trophy and seeps into Clark’s bedroom. It enters his mind and feeds him the memory of his adventures as Superboy on Zoltam. Superboy had ventured to that planet and defeated a monstrous flying gnmod. But unbeknownst to him, the spirit of the gnmod had taken shelter in the metal trophy presented to Superboy by the people of Zoltam.

Now, the Dwalu appears in ’s bedroom and blasts him with his Xaka sword’s energy. Chief Parker and Lois hear ’s scream and come up to see his smouldering bed.

Superman is instantly teleported to a grassland and comes face to face with the Dwalu. The Dwalu reveals that he is really the Gnmod and has gained this form from Superboy’s memories. He will now have his revenge on Superboy. The battle begins. The Gnmod uses the Xaka sword to blast Superman. Superman tries to defeat him by trickery because his super-strength pales before that of the Dwalu. Still he manages to separate him from the sword and throws it around the world in a controlled trajectory. He hacks at the Dwalu’s neck but is progressively weakening. This is when the sword comes back and reaches Superman. He points it upon the Dwalu’s head and asks him to surrender. The Dwalu accepts his defeat and threatens to return.

Superman returns home and appears under his bed. Lois is relieved to see him. He makes up a story and quickly dispels her suspicions.
name: Attack of the Ultimate Warrior!

Overview

This is it, the beginning of the next Annihilation main event! In the PROLOGUE, the Phalanx launched a sneak attack on the Kree Empire. In NOVA, QUASAR, STAR-LORD and WRAITH, heroes separated by distance but united by willpower took their first steps to liberating a galaxy in peril. Now all the threads begin to weave together -- and if you thought the surprises were over, think again! What are the Phalanx really after? What new players will change the game? And what last-page reveal will leave your jaw hanging?

Grab your weapon and join the fight for freedom with the powerhouse creative team of writers Dan Abnett & Andy Lanning and penciler Tom Raney (ULTIMATE X-MEN)!
name: No Way Out

description:
The Silver Surfer delves alone into the furthest depths of the void; tangling with organ-stealing pirates, demonic beasts and a race of alien aristocrats. Everyone's favorite Cosmic Wanderer discovers that even in the midst of a galactic utopia, horror is never far away...

With electrifying artwork by the dynamic Tan Eng Huat (Doom Patrol, Batman) and an endlessly inventive script by Simon Spurrier - the writer behind the sold-out Gutsville - In Thy Name promises to be this fall most spectacular Alien Extravaganza!

Summary

Alone in space, the Silver Surfer contemplates the nature and horror of life when he is suddenly attacked. It is a group of Organpirates attempting to capture him and sell his parts. But before the Surfer retaliates, the pirates retreat. He is soon invited on to a massive ship that has scared the pirates away.

Inside he meets Ruqtar Koil, a member of the Ama Collective, a peaceful organization that lets other planets and races join them in hopes of creating a Utopia. The Surfer is brought to Ama-Prime, a paradise and homeworld to the Collective, to meet their Empress. After a short stay, they ask the Surfer for his assistance with a 'beast made of ghosts' on the planet Brekknis.

On Brekknis, the beast awakens and starts it's attack as it does everyday. The Surfer challenges it, making the locals believe that he is their savior.
name: In Thy Name: Part 1

description:
Promotional comic for the game.

The issue starts with two men conversing on the yellow line (a monorail used for transportation) one a hero and one a reguler bystander. While another hero behind him flys into a hazard zone once they reach their stop. The hero who conversed with the man going by the name Thunder-clap also heads in to make a name for himself. Thunder-clap who needs alpha clearance soon sees the door open with two badly wounded heroes coming out. He jumps through the door before it closes saying "how bad can it be". Once in he is attacked by two thugs who he pursues. After chaseing one thug into an alley way he sees the two heroes War Witch and her sidekick Apex fighting against a gang of the same thugs. Thunder-clap proceeds to aid them in the fight when the fight is over they are called to assist the Freedom Phalanx against a 5th Column threat. With a brutal battle following which the heroes are soon to overcome and proceed to disable to bombs set around the building. When a robot soldier comes and the heroes are near beaten when Statesmen comes and saves them. Then explains the history of the Fifth Column.

description: All-new X-Men series! During her time as part of the X-MEN, the woman known as ROGUE has been many things -- fighter, friend, soldier, lover…and now, daughter. When an X-Men mission brings Rogue back to her childhood home in Mississippi, she comes face to face with the demons in her past…and a terrible secret that has haunted her family since her birth!
name: Going Rogue, Part 1

Lois Lane: A fine honeymoon this is Superman- keeping me a prisoner in this glass cage! Look how Lana Lang is gloating!

Superman: It's for your own good, Lois Dear! Now that you're my wife it's my duty to protect you from my enemies. You'll always be safe in my bullet-proof auto-car!
name: Superman and Lois Lane, Newlyweds!

description:
Rick Parker and Stefan Petrucha, the team behind the hit TALES FROM THE CRYPT #8, get together again, this time taking on Harry Potter! Following the murder of their mentor Dumb-As-A-Door by the seemingly traitorous Barista Frappe; Harry Potty, Don Measley and Whiny Stranger must find a way to defeat the nose-less lord Value-Mart (He-Whose-Prices-Can't-Be-Beat) and his followers the Odor Eaters in order to avenge the death of Harry Potty's parents and bring balance to the world of magic.

Available in softcover and hardcover.
name: Harry Potty and the Deathly Boring

The team that brought you the best-selling Diary of a Stinky Dead Kid cuts up the best-selling series starring love-sick vampires and jealous werewolves! The "Twilight Saga" gets sliced up in this unauthorized parody of the blockbuster book and movie series! For fans sick of glittery vampires and wonky werewolves, here's an hilarious antidote.

Available in softcover and hardcover.
name: Breaking Down
